  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released\u00a001/04/2016 4:15PM UTC 10:15 AM CT</p><p>This is a minor update to address bugs and add minor features.</p><p><strong>Customer Sync on Tickets</strong></p><p>In some cases, when\u00a0creating a new customer on a\u00a0repair ticket, the customer would not show as attached to the ticket\u00a0until the repair device\u00a0is added. This was due to a race condition in the customer sync process, and it has been resolved.</p><p><strong>Deleting Ticket Notes</strong></p><p>Fixed an issue with removing\u00a0ticket notes on a new ticket (not yet saved for the first time).</p><p><strong>Ticket Edit Lock Upgrades</strong></p><p>RepairQ protects against saving\u00a0conflicting edits of the same ticket, where two different users save the same ticket at the same time. This protection has been extended to the scenario where the same user saves the same ticket from two different\u00a0windows.</p><p><strong>Ticket Import Upgrades</strong></p><p>Three new fields have been added to the ticket import feature:</p><ul><li><p>Repair Cost Estimate</p></li><li><p>Repair Device Location (or Bin #)</p></li><li><p>Ticket\u00a0Notes</p></li></ul><p><strong>Inventory Search +\u00a0Bulk Edit</strong></p><p>Fixed an issue where the bulk edit button would initiate the &quot;print labels&quot; action if you performed the following sequence:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li><p>Use the global search to pull up an inventory item by SKU match (Where RepairQ\u00a0places you on the item page rather than a\u00a0search results page)</p></li><li><p>Select items to bulk edit</p></li><li><p>Click bulk edit button</p></li></ol><p>Now when the above sequence is performed the bulk edit action will occur, rather than the print labels action.</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
